SECTION. Keeping debian system clean
====================================

- Remove obsolete libs: 'deborphan' and 'apt-get remove `deborphan`'
- Purge obsolete packages: 'dpkg --get-selections | grep 'deinstall$' and 
                           'dpkg --purge `dpkg --get-selections | grep 'deinstall$' | cut -f1`'

- Check that myprogs repository is in sync: 'sudo myprogs check'

- Check for obsolete packages with: 'aptitude search ?obsolete'

SECTION. Backups
================

SCOPE:

- The following Directories to be backed up:
/home/zamar/work
/var/lib/myprogs
/data/pics

SETUP:

- Create target directory in another server or usbdisk
- If using another server, setup key authentication between servers (keys in ~/.ssh)
- Install sshbackup from ~/work/src/sshbackup
- Edit and install config from ~/work/config/sshbackup

EXECUTION:

- /data/pics : Once a year (01/01/20xx)

mount-usb
sshbackup /etc/sshbackup/meripeto_pics_snapshot.backup
sshbackup /etc/sshbackup/meripeto_pics_sync.backup
umount-usb

- /home/zamar/work, /var/lib/myprogs : After significant development or changes have been made since last backup.

mount-usb
sshbackup /etc/sshbackup/meripeto_work_snapshot.backup
sshbackup /etc/sshbackup/meripeto_work_sync.backup
umount-usb

